<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-23T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-23T10:00:00-05:00" n="112" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d112">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">868.01/570: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador to the Greek Government in
                                    Exile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-23T18:00:00+03:00">May
                                        23, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received May 24—1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Greek 168. My Greek 166, May 22, 6 p.m. Mr. Papandreou has been
                                entrusted with the formation of the Government of National Unity. It
                                is reported that the number of portfolios which seems certain to be
                                large and their apportionment among the various parties and
                                organizations was clearly settled at the last meeting of the
                                conference. As the delegates are now all in Cairo it is believed
                                that Papandreou will complete his task very shortly.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>